{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ae16852d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Multivariate BMM for n = 3, ..., N models\n",
    "\n",
    "### Author: Alexandra Semposki\n",
    "\n",
    "### Date: 11 October 2022"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0a546b5b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This tutorial notebook focuses on the N model case for the Multivariate BMM mixing technique. Let's get started!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "e12dd7ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib \n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "from matplotlib.ticker import AutoMinorLocator\n",
    "\n",
    "matplotlib.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    'font.family': 'serif',\n",
    "    'text.usetex': True,\n",
    "})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c3f01ddf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We import the models we'll need from the package SAMBA (wrapped with Taweret) and import the Multivariate mixer from the `gaussian.py` file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "d9adcfd7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('../../../')\n",
    "from Taweret.models.samba_models import *\n",
    "from Taweret.mix.gaussian import *"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "68aaa00c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We pick the truncation orders we would like to investigate in our model mixing, and select which model will be using which truncation order. We're considering a toy model, which can be expanded in powers of a coupling constant $g$ or in $1/g$. This means that we need two different series: `loworder` represents the series expansion at small-$g$, and `highorder` the series expansion at large-$g$. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "803065a9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#list of models to mix\n",
    "orders=[3,5,7]\n",
    "model_1 = Loworder(order=orders[0])\n",
    "model_2 = Loworder(order=orders[1])\n",
    "model_3 = Highorder(order=orders[2])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "753e88f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we compile these models into a dictionary that we can pass into Taweret."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "c477bd1e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "{'1': <Taweret.models.samba_models.Loworder object at 0x0000022BA57F89A0>, '2': <Taweret.models.samba_models.Loworder object at 0x0000022BA57F8A00>, '3': <Taweret.models.samba_models.Highorder object at 0x0000022BA57F89D0>} <class 'dict'>\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#dict of models\n",
    "models = {\n",
    "    \"1\": model_1,\n",
    "    \"2\": model_2,\n",
    "    \"3\": model_3\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(models, type(models))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0cd69bf3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we would like to see the models we just saved, so we evaluate them at the input points we choose and plot each model individually, along with its 68\\% uncertainties."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "3a37ab43",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#predict functions for the plot\n",
    "g = np.linspace(1e-6, 1.0, 100)\n",
    "predict = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in models.keys():\n",
    "    predict.append(models[i].evaluate(g))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4d36a698",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now let's plot!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "11b64a37",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x22ba6875160>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#basic plot to check choices\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)\n",
    "ax = plt.axes()\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0.0,1.0)\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(1.2,3.2)\n",
    "ax.tick_params(axis='x', direction='in')\n",
    "ax.tick_params(axis='y', direction='in')\n",
    "ax.locator_params(nbins=8)\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())\n",
    "ax.set_title('SAMBA Models (N=3)')\n",
    "\n",
    "#truth\n",
    "ax.plot(g, TrueModel().evaluate(g)[0].flatten(), 'k', label='True')\n",
    "\n",
    "#colour wheel\n",
    "colors = ['r', 'm', 'b']\n",
    "lines = ['dashed', 'dotted']\n",
    "\n",
    "#models\n",
    "for i in range(len(predict)):\n",
    "    ax.plot(g, predict[i][0].flatten(), color=colors[i], linestyle=lines[0], label=r'$N_s={}$'.format(orders[i]))\n",
    "\n",
    "#uncertainties\n",
    "for i in range(len(predict)):\n",
    "    ax.plot(g, predict[i][0].flatten() - predict[i][1].flatten(), color=colors[i], linestyle=lines[1])\n",
    "    ax.plot(g, predict[i][0].flatten() + predict[i][1].flatten(), color=colors[i], linestyle=lines[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "999b4196",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we would like to mix. We call the Multivariate() class from Taweret and send it the input space and the models we created, instantiate an object, and then use the `predict` method in the Multivariate() class to mix the models and send back the mean, intervals, and standard deviation of the mixed model. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "5566589c",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#call bivariate method and mix\n",
    "mixed = Multivariate(g, models)\n",
    "posterior_draws, mixed_mean, mixed_intervals, std_dev = mixed.predict(ci=68)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "c5dd1a5a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x22ba6921cd0>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#plot to check mixed model\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,6), dpi=100)\n",
    "ax = plt.axes()\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0.0,1.0)\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(1.2,3.2)\n",
    "ax.tick_params(axis='x', direction='in')\n",
    "ax.tick_params(axis='y', direction='in')\n",
    "ax.locator_params(nbins=8)\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())\n",
    "ax.set_title('SAMBA Models (N=3)')\n",
    "\n",
    "#truth\n",
    "ax.plot(g, TrueModel().evaluate(g)[0].flatten(), 'k', label='True')\n",
    "\n",
    "#colour wheel\n",
    "colors = ['r', 'm', 'b']\n",
    "lines = ['dashed', 'dotted']\n",
    "\n",
    "#models\n",
    "for i in range(len(predict)):\n",
    "    ax.plot(g, predict[i][0].flatten(), color=colors[i], linestyle=lines[0], label=r'$N_s={}$'.format(orders[i]))\n",
    "\n",
    "#uncertainties\n",
    "for i in range(len(predict)):\n",
    "    ax.plot(g, predict[i][0].flatten() - predict[i][1].flatten(), color=colors[i], linestyle=lines[1])\n",
    "    ax.plot(g, predict[i][0].flatten() + predict[i][1].flatten(), color=colors[i], linestyle=lines[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "#mean and intervals\n",
    "ax.plot(g, mixed_mean, 'g', label='Mixed model')\n",
    "ax.fill_between(g, mixed_mean-std_dev, mixed_mean+std_dev,\n",
    "                        zorder=i-5, facecolor='green', alpha=0.2, lw=0.6)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f459d791",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Excellent! We have a mixed model for these three individual series expansions. Now we can add a GP as the third model (or more) if we desire. In Taweret, the user has all control over the models that they write to input. Hence, one can design any model one wishes to use, as long as it possesses the ability to produce a mean and a set of uncertainties at each point in the input space."
   ]
  }
 ],
